The paper deals with the capacity of state-dependent channels with feedback, which is a topic in information theory (cs.IT). The use of variable-length coding schemes suggests that the paper may also be relevant to the subfield of coding theory (cs.CC). The analysis of different cases with state information revealed in different ways suggests that the paper may also be relevant to the subfield of signal processing (cs.SI). The use of necessary and sufficient conditions suggests that the paper may also be relevant to the subfield of algorithms and data structures (cs.DS). Finally, the comparison with the fixed-length case suggests that the paper may also be relevant to the subfield of machine learning (cs.LG).
